news.title: Bengaluru: Residents of Kithaganur and Halehalli panchayat demands basic amenities
news.para: VP Krishna, the Founder of the Federation, emphasised the urgency of these demands, stating, “Our daily lives are severely disrupted due to poor infrastructure and lack of basic amenities.

news.title: Karnataka: Quarry owners opposes one-time settlement scheme
news.para: The Cabinet’s decision is aimed at collecting the pending penalty amounting to Rs 6,105 crore from the miners in the state.

news.title: Agarwal Holdings acquires land parcel for Rs 455 crore in Mumbai’s Juhu
news.para: The transaction was finalized and registered in November 2024, with a stamp duty of Rs 27.30 crore and registration charges amounting to Rs 30,000.

news.title: Blackstone acquires LOGOS India’s 5 million sq ft warehousing assets for Rs 1,725 crore
news.para: The deal indicates Blackstone’s continued focus on strengthening its presence in India’s rapidly expanding logistics and supply chain infrastructure sector.

news.title: Ayodhya's Vashisth Kunj residential scheme offers plots at premium rates
news.para: According to the latest trend, barring Lucknow, prices of properties floated by various agencies under the housing department in the Awadh region are on the higher side in Ayodhya.

news.title: Noida International Airport conducts validation flight in Gautam Buddha Nagar
news.para: The validation flight was conducted by an IndiGo A320 passenger aircraft in the presence of civil aviation minister Kinjarapu Rammohan Naidu.

news.title: Civic authorities undertake drive to raze 58 illegal buildings in Kalyan-Dombivli limits
news.para: The Kalyan Dombivli Municipal Corporation (KDMC), in a release, said the drive was in compliance with a Bombay High Court order that declared the structures illegal.

news.title: BMC issues speaking order against construction firm for violating air pollution norms in Kandivli
news.para: The R-South ward issued a notice earlier in Jan this year, and the developer responded, claiming they were adhering to the guidelines. However, following a complaint, the site was inspected recently, and the BMC found that the site was not adhering to several pollution guidelines.

news.title: Hong Kong's ESR Group to spin-off logistics assets in $289.2 million REIT offering
news.para: In December 2022, the real estate company proposed that its logistics assets be spun off and listed separately on the Shanghai Stock Exchange as a publicly traded infrastructure securities investment fund.

news.title: Gurugram civic body to terminate nine agencies for lapses in construction waste collection
news.para: MCG has now proposed a new initiative to collect approximately 5 lakh metric tonnes of construction waste scattered across city roads and public spaces, with an estimated cost of Rs 9 crore.

news.title: Kerala government undecided on taking back 61 acres of idle land in Technopark phase-III
news.para: Principal secretary (industries) APM Mohammed Hanish told TOI that the industries department will hold a detailed consultation with the IT department soon to decide on the underutilized land in Phase III.

news.title: Hootagalli civic body expands with inclusion of 45 new layouts from Muda
news.para: Currently, the CMC is providing service to 33 layouts, including three industrial areas of Hinakal, Koorgalli, and Belwadi.

news.title: Indore civic body turns to public shaming to recover dues from tax defaulters
news.para: As of November 30, the IMC collected around Rs 575 crore. With over three months remaining in the financial year, officials are confident of achieving the Rs 1,000 crore target.

news.title: Kochi civic body fails to disburse PMAY and Life Mission funds
news.para: "So far as we could learn, around 80 beneficiaries are awaiting the release of funds by the local body. On inquiry, we found out that the corporation's bank account, which is being operated for the scheme, has around Rs 28 crore in it," said corporation UDF parliamentary party secretary M G Aristotle.

news.title: Over 13,000 applicants benefit from property regularization under PM-UDAY in Delhi
news.para: The Prime Minister-Unauthorised Colonies in Delhi Awas Adhikar Yojana (PM-UDAY) scheme aims to grant ownership rights to residents of 1,731 unauthorised colonies in the national capital.

news.title: NHB tightens oversight on HFCs after Aviom India Housing fraud
news.para: NHB, which has been conducting periodic inspections at HFCs, has called for stricter compliance during those audits, people in the know said.

news.title: Only 5,648 homes allotted to migrant workers under ARHC scheme in 4.5 years
news.para: This is less than 7% of the 83,534 houses that were identified for the scheme when it was approved by the Cabinet.

news.title: Credai Gujarat submits memorandums to district collectors opposing proposed jantri rates
news.para: Claiming that the jantri rates proposed were not derived scientifically, the real estate developers and farmers across the state have been opposing the govt's proposal.

news.title: Bombay HC upholds tenants’ right to redevelop dilapidated Kalbadevi building
news.para: They quashed and set aside Mhada's July 8 order to the landlords to submit a redevelopment proposal and the July 10 letter of intent (LoI) permitting them to undertake the building's redevelopment.

news.title: Gurugram: All towers of Chintels Paradiso declared unsafe, set for demolition
news.para: In its latest report, Central Building Research Institute (CBRI) has found that Tower B has severe structural flaws, including widespread cracks, corroded reinforcement bars and substandard concrete, findings similar to those in the other towers.
